{"abstract": "Investors are pushing up shares of Imperial Tobacco on the possibility that it could acquire brands cast off in a Reynolds-Lorillard deal, but an acquisition would be a stretch financially, and the long-term benefits may be scant.", "web_url": "https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/07/11/imperial-tobaccos-ambitions-challenge-its-balance-sheet/", "snippet": "Investors are pushing up shares of Imperial Tobacco on the possibility that it could acquire brands cast off in a Reynolds-Lorillard deal, but an acquisition would be a stretch financially, and the long-term benefits may be scant.", "lead_paragraph": "Investors think Imperial Tobacco has much to gain from a possible $56 billion merger of its United States peers, Reynolds American and Lorillard. The combination would require a large sale of assets to assuage antitrust regulators, and these forced sales could present bargains for Imperial. The snag is that Imperial is short of cash \u2013 and the assets available may not be that attractive.", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "xlarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/07/11/business/dealbook/dbpix-imperial/dbpix-imperial-articleLarge.jpg", "height": 381, "width": 600, "subType": "xlarge", "crop_name": "articleLarge", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/07/11/business/dealbook/dbpix-imperial/dbpix-imperial-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": 600, "xlargeheight": 381}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/07/11/business/dealbook/dbpix-imperial/dbpix-imperial-jumbo.jpg", "height": 651, "width": 1024, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/07/11/business/dealbook/dbpix-imperial/dbpix-imperial-superJumbo.jpg", "height": 1301, "width": 2048, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}